================================================================================
TIER 0 — FREE LICENSE (Non-Commercial & Micro-Indie)
================================================================================

The Software may be used at no charge, subject to ALL of the following
conditions:

1. ELIGIBLE USE. Free use is permitted exclusively for:

   a) NON-COMMERCIAL projects that generate zero revenue:
      - Personal projects, experiments, and learning
      - Educational and academic work (students, teachers, institutions)
      - Open-source projects (OSI-approved license, non-monetized)
      - Game jams and hackathons, including prize-winning entries
      - Portfolio projects and public demonstrations
      - Internal prototypes and proof-of-concept work

   b) MICRO-INDIE commercial projects where the total gross annual revenue
      across ALL products using the Software is below $25,000 USD (or
      equivalent in any currency, calculated at the date of measurement).

      Revenue is measured across the licensee's entire business entity,
      not per-product. Once this threshold is exceeded, a paid license
      (Tier 1 or above) is required within 30 days.

2. ATTRIBUTION REQUIRED. All projects using the Free License must display
   the following attribution in a clearly visible location (credits screen,
   about page, game description, README, or in-app notice):

       "Audio powered by ChiptuneSynth — 8Binami.com"

   Attribution must be human-readable and reasonably prominent. It may not
   be hidden, obfuscated, or placed exclusively in source code comments
   for end-user-facing commercial releases.

3. SINGLE ENTITY. The Free License is granted to a single individual or
   organization and may not be shared across separate legal entities.

4. NO SUBLICENSING. You may not redistribute, resell, or grant sub-licenses
   for the Software to third parties.

5. NO REVERSE ENGINEERING. Decompiling, deobfuscating, disassembling, or
   attempting to reconstruct the source code of the Software in any form is
   strictly prohibited.

6. NO TAMPERING. You may not modify, patch, or tamper with the obfuscated
   distributed files. Extension through the documented public API is
   permitted.

7. GAME JAM TO COMMERCIAL. Free use is permitted for game jam submissions.
   If a submission is subsequently commercialized, the $25,000/year revenue
   threshold applies from the date commercial revenue begins.


